<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101484495113962></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101484495113962><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=journal.html?user=2076&mid=101484495113962>Hunting in ButcherBlock Mountains</a> <a id=fs8 href=journal.html?user=2076&mid=101484495113962#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=76256><span id=Scholar>Gorfrey Defender of Justice</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>17 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Feb 27th 4:23 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hidden behind the wooded crest of a hill, the two young adventurers gazed intently at the dwarf camp hidden among the mountains of Faydwer.<br><br>&quot;Who are they?&quot; whispered Arione.<br><br>&quot;Bandits,&quot; replied Gorfrey in hushed tones.&nbsp;&nbsp;&quot;Former members of one of the mining guilds in Kaladim who have strayed from the true path of Brell.&quot;<br><br>&quot;Can we take them?&quot; asked Arione.  The young wood elf was clearly eager to pick a fight.<br><br>The somewhat older dwarf scatched his beard thoughtfully.  &quot;I don't know - there are many of them, and they are skilled in combat.  I think we will both have to use magic.  I will lull those two in the tents, and you will have to root the one with the wooden leg.  Then we can take take the one on the far right.&quot;  <br><br>&quot;I understand. Then repeat with the others?&quot; <br><br>&quot;Yes, then we can work our way through the lot of them.&quot;  Gorfrey smiled at his new friend.  This young ranger was eager to learn from him, and had proved an adept student.<br><br>&quot;Let us begin then,&quot; said Arione as he crawled forward over the crest of the hill, remaining carefully hidden from view.  <br><br>Gorfrey quietly invoked the power of Brell, and two of the bandits were lulled into a semi-conscious stupor.  He then rose and fired an arrow into the shoulder of the closest bandit.  <br><br>The bandit cried out in pain.  Nearby, the bandit leader Peg Leg saw Gorfrey and drew his dagger from its sheath.  As he started to run, vines near his feet slowly wrapped themselves around his ankles, slowing him down.<br><br>Seeing his successful spell take affect, Arione drew back his own arrow and let it fly, striking the bandit Gorfrey had wounded.  He then quickly drew a second one and watched with satisfaction as it struck the writhing bandit in the leg.<br><br>Cursing and in pain, the bandit struggled up the hill and closed upon Gorfrey and Arione.<br><br>Unknown to them, Qued had been sleeping off the previous evening's drinking in the bushes where he had fallen after passing out.  The screams of his fellow highwaymen caused the hung-over dwarf to suddenly awake with a start.  <br><br>Realizing he was behind them and that they did not see him, Qued leaped onto the back of the elven ranger, slashing with his dagger.  Arione reacted quickly, grabbing his sword and shield as he kicked the shorter dwarf in the chest.<br><br>Gorfrey now had two of the bandits attacking him, and a third was running towards him.  &quot;Arione!&quot; he shouted. &quot;Cast the root spell NOW!&quot;  <br><br>Nothing.  &quot;ARIONE!&quot; Gorfrey bellowed as the third dwarf bandit ran up and started pounding on the paladin with his fists. <br><br>&quot;I'm here!  There was another one we didn't see!&quot; replied the ranger as he blocked Qued's thrusts with his shield.<br><br>&quot;Run, Arione!  Save yourself!&quot; Gorfrey shouted as he slashed a bandit deeply across the chest, causing him to drop lifelessly to the ground.  Two more to go.  <br><br>Run to where? thought Arione as he suddenly realized he had no idea where he was.  Gorfrey had led him to the camp, and now he had no idea which way to go.  Seeing a stone tower in the distance, Arione sprinted towards it with both Qued and a female dwarf following close behind.<br><br>Gorfrey had slain yet another of the bandits, but he was quickly tiring and had taken a lot of punishment.  He knew that a dwarven guard post was not too far away, but he also knew that it was highly likely he would run into goblins along the way.  He staggered along the path, knowing that he would have to chance it.  Luckily, the goblin camp was deserted. <br><br>Closely followed by two bandits, Gorfrey pounded on the door of the guard hut on the road to Kaladim.  &quot;Open the door!  The bandits are right behind me!&quot;<br><br>The door flew open and the heavily armored dwarven guards grabbed Gorfrey and threw him inside on the rug.  The bandits did not see them coming until it was too late.<br><br>After taking some time to recover from his wounds, Gorfrey thanked the guards for their kindness and care and set out again towards the now empty bandit camp.  <br><br>I must find Arione, he thought.  I hope he is safe.   <br><br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>Gorfrey<br>Paladin of the 16th Season, Legions of Might<br>Zebuxoruk Server<br><br>Paladin of the 7th season<br>Test server<br>"Dark elves.... I hate these guys"</td></tr>
