<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=10147618696838></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f10147618696838><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=journal.html?user=2076&mid=10147618696838>Encounters with evil</a> <a id=fs8 href=journal.html?user=2076&mid=10147618696838#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=76256><span id=Scholar>Gorfrey Defender of Justice</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>17 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Feb 26th 5:18 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>The traveller spotted the inn across the great open expanse of the Western Common Lands.&nbsp;&nbsp;The light was on, and there seemed to be activity inside.  Maybe now I can get some rest, he thought.  The journey from Kaladim had been a long one. The young dwarven paladin Gorfrey was covered with sweat and dust as he strode through the door of the inn.<br><br>&quot;Barkeep, an ale, if you please,&quot; he shouted in a weary voice.  He dropped his packs upon the floor and clambered onto a stool.  <br><br>The barkeep eyed the young dwarf warily.  &quot;Here you go - that will be six silver pieces.  No tab here for you.&quot;<br><br>Shrugging off the attempted insult, Gorfrey didn't even bother to blow the foam off the top of the tankard as was his custom.  Taking a long deep drink, he slammed the empty mug back on the counter.  He quickly downed five more, after paying the barkeep in advance for all five.  Tired from his long voyage across the sea and not thinking about anything but his fatigue and the stout ales in front of him, the young paladin  did not see the hidden danger. <br><br>&quot;I have travelled far and I am weary. Do you have a room for me?  Or is my money no good to you, sir?&quot; <br><br>&quot;We have a room for you,&quot; the barkeep said ominously.  &quot;But first you will have to speak to Zytl.&quot;<br><br>&quot;And who is Zytl?  Is he the innkeeper?&quot; the dwarf asked, beginning to sense through his alcoholic fog that something was amiss.<br><br>Just then the dark elf dragoon Zytl burst through the door behind the dwarf.  Gorfrey had not quite gotten his trusty bastard sword out of its sheath when the sneering Zytl stuck his first blow, and then his second.  Slowed by the alcohol and weakened by his wounds, Gorfrey staggered out the door and began to flee towards the road where he had seen a human guard post.  <br><br>If I can make it to the guards, surely they will protect me, he thought.  Just a little further.<br><br>Sure enough, the toll booth and its gate loomed ahead of him in the darkness.  Collapsing at the feet of one of the guards, Gorfrey gasped &quot;Dark elf... attacked me... please....&quot;<br><br>The guard fingered his Freeport Militia tunic and looked down at the slowly dying dwarf.  He looked up to see the dark elf coming to finish the job.<br><br>&quot;Save yourself, paladin,&quot; the guard muttered.  &quot;Where is your god Brell now?&quot;<br><br>/OOC on<br><br>Pusbag,<br><br>Sorry it took so long to respond to your post on my journal.  Been busy with work and school.  Hope you like my first entry!<br><br>/OOC off<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>Gorfrey<br>Paladin of the 16th Season, Legions of Might<br>Zebuxoruk Server<br><br>Paladin of the 7th season<br>Test server<br>"Dark elves.... I hate these guys"</td></tr>
