<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101433719237275></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101433719237275><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=journal.html?user=2076&mid=101433719237275>Pusbag and Gezz are Summoned</a> <a id=fs8 href=journal.html?user=2076&mid=101433719237275#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=60669><span id=Guru>Mugali the Mighty</span></a>, <span id=Guru>Guru</span><br><span id=notbold>400 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Feb 21st 7:20 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>The Iksar and the Troll spent a fortnight traveling through the Dreadlands and then the Burning Woods.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Iksar Gezz had given Pusbag permission to use his magical skill.  Of course, this was to defend Gezz only.  Pusbag was delighted to put his shamanistic talents to use once again, without fizzles no less, and proceeded to slaughter a large feast for himself.<br><br>As they traveled, the Burning Woods soon gave way to a rocky, desolate landscape.  The sky burned with red fire.  Dark clouds hung above the two travelers.  The sky itself seemed to burn.  Pusbag and Gezz climbed higher into the rocks, and soon found themselves tranversing around pools and fissures of magma.  The molten rock added to their trevails and they progressed slowly.<br><br>&quot;Gezz, where are we, I have not been to these lands?&quot;, Pusbag asked his companion.<br><br>&quot;These are the Skyfire Mountains of Kunark.  Only the greatest adventurers come to these lands, the bravest souls.  Perhaps you will have a chance to test your bravery this day.&quot;, Gezz replied as he leaned on his staff.  <br><br>No sooner had he finished when a screaching cry rose from the east.  Pusbag turned and to his astonishment saw a drake flying rapidly in their direction.  Instead of the normal leathery wings possesed by most dragonkind, this one had four clear wings, much like a monstrous dragonfly.  The beast flew in low and attacked Pusbag with it's massive claws.<br><br>Gezz shouted,&quot;A chormadrac, fight!&quot;, and began to cast a spell.  The beast slashed and hacked at Pusbag.  Some of the strikes got through, but, the Troll had faced greater foes in the past.  He cast choking spell on the chromadrac, but it resisted and cast a spell of it's own!  Pusbag could feel his blood begin to boil.  Soon his entire body was filled with intense pain.  As Gezz's spells took effect, the beast slowed down.  Enraged, while at the same time enjoying his pain, Pusbag began to land crushing blows against the beasts flank.  It fell from the sky and two of it's wings were rended on the sharp rocks.  Gezz sent a bolt of magic into the drake as Pusbag delivered a final blow with his mace.  <br><br>As the chromadrac breathed it's last, Pusbag sat down and began to rock back and forth in agony.  The spell the creature had cast still boiled thoughout the blood in his body.  Gezz walked over and cast several spells on the Troll and soon the enchantment faded.  <br><br>After awile Pusbag looked at him shrwedly and plainly stated,&quot;You are no Iksar, you are an enchanter!  I know you!  You are....&quot;.  <br><br>Pusbag had no chance to finish.  Suddenly the world faded before the two adventurers.  Pusbag felt himself flying over the landscape, bumping off of rocks, tumbling through the air.  He and the Iksar were promptly dropped to the ground at the feet of a large Dragon.  The Dragon's skin was green and dulled with age, yet power emenated from it.  It also possesed four clear wings, like those of the chromadrac, but was much larger and fearsome.<br><br>The Dragon hissed, it's breath stinking and virulent,&quot;What brings lesser beings here, to slay my kin?&quot;.  The Dragon rested it's gaze upon Pusbag and Gezz as they stood up.<br><br>Gezz spoke,&quot;Eldrig the Old, I bring you treaties from the Empire of the Iksar.&quot;, Gezz stated as he bowed slowly,&quot;Would you here this message?&quot;<br><br>Eldrig thought for a moment,&quot;Speak you words, scaled one, the other will remain silent in my precense, lest I slay him.&quot;, the Dragon looked closely at Pusbag, who in turn did not move.<br><br>Gezz spoke,&quot;I have been sent by none other than Grandmaster Glox, the newly appointed leader of Cabilis.  Our words are this:  The Iksar have long suffered from our defeat at the hands of Dragonkind.  Yet, from this suffering we have learned a most valuable lesson, patience.  Long have we waited for the day when we would rise to power yet again, and our day has come.  The nations of sofskins fall before us and our power grows.  Yet Dragonkind dissapear from history.  They venture forth no more.  They waste away in the homes and lairs.  Kunark belongs to the empire of the Iksar, and we will have it no other way.  Cabilis demands the surrender of all Dragonkind on Kunark.  They are to leave within a fortnight, leaving behind all their stolen treasures; otherwise they will suffer the wrath of the Iksar!&quot;<br><br>Gezz finished his stunning pronouncement by spitting on the ground at the foot of Eldrig.  Pusbag began to slowly back off.  This Iksar, or what ever he is, was clearly quite insane.  Eldrig did not move for nearly a minute.  His skin began to turn a deeper shade of green and his eyes glowed with hatred.<br><br>Gezz turned to Pusbag,&quot;Run you stupid Troll, you services are ended!  Seek your vengeance or become a slave to the Iksar!  Do not let your ambition lead to disgrace again!  Run!&quot;.<br><br>Gezz turned and began casting a spell at Eldrig.  Eldrig sent a tremendous bolt of power into the Iksar.  Gezz's spell sent a flash of colors into the air about Eldrig, blinding and stunning him.  Pusbag summoned up the spirit of the wolf and began to run.  And run he did, faster than he ever had before.  Behind him, he could here the thunder of spells as Eldrig and Gezz fought each other.  Pusbag was free of his geas, for a moment he thought of his revenge, his justice.  Quickly thoughts of vengence were replaced by fear and he ran even faster.<br>&nbsp;<br>Judd Jaggedoak <br>(deceased)<br>Wood Elf Ranger<br><br><br><br><br></td></tr>
