<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101424252632094></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101424252632094><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=journal.html?user=2076&mid=101424252632094>Strange Books and Strange Spells</a> <a id=fs8 href=journal.html?user=2076&mid=101424252632094#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=90070><span id=Scholar>Fourletters</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>29 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Feb 20th 5:02 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>A small gnome sat down by the coast of the oasis, darkness already falling as the sun set behind mountains of sand. He could feel the sand cooling gradually under him as he lit his lantern and began to attempt to decipher the Tier'Dal book he had found. He fliped through the pages slowly, making notes on the translations in his native tongue in as many places as possible. He finally recognized one of the spells as a spell which would summon a skeletal servent of so medicore strength.<br><br>&quot;Now why would any inteligent necromancer have such a low power spell in a book with all these spells I can't even hope to understand?&quot;<br><br>With a lack of anything better to do, the gnome began to slowly copy the spell into his own book, in his own tongue. He stood to cast the spell, darklines of mana flowing around his body as he chanted the spell. He tossed the chips of bones on the ground to serve as the focus for the spell and said the final binding words...<br><br>Nothing happened.<br><br>He stared at the pile of bone chips on the ground as the mana feld the area.&nbsp;&nbsp;His spell hadn't fizzled, he knew that, he had said the words exactly at they were written.  He compared the writings in the two books again, and swearing quietly, wishing he had spent more time listening when he had been taught the dark tongue. Suddenly he heard a noise behind him and spun around to see an orc dressed in platemail running at him full tilt. He began casting the spell again, hoping it would work and the servent would engage the orc as he cast other spells. The dark lines of mana flowed again from his hands wrapping around his body. He completed the spell just as the orc reached him and nearly fainted from shock as the orc seemed to explode into flying mass of gore and blood, splattering the little gnome and all of his things.<br><br>&quot;What in the name of.....&quot;<br><br>The gnome stopped as before him stood a skeleton dressed in Platemail, standing ready and at his command.  The gnomes jaw dropped.<br><br>&quot;Is this what I-Did that orc just-WOW!&quot;<br><br>The gnome grabbed his quill and began to write in his thankfully not-so-bloody spellbook, writing notes on the incantation, not resting until the sun had nearly risen.<br><br>The gnome thought to himself as he prepared to sleep in one of the many hunts along the oasis,<br><br>'Tomorrow I shall begin my travel to Kurnak and with the aid of this spell, the Iksar will be sorry they ever existed in Norrath!'<br><br>With that final thought in mind he slowly drifted to sleep.<br><br>Azuthe (Name Pending) <br>Gnome Necromancer <br>Former 24th, now 23rd again Circle of the Dark Arts<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed Feb 20 17:04:01 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
