<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101418201528776></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101418201528776><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=journal.html?user=2076&mid=101418201528776>Of Lore and Pain, Answers</a> <a id=fs8 href=journal.html?user=2076&mid=101418201528776#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=120456><span id=Guru>QueenUsula</span></a>, <span id=Guru>Guru</span><br><span id=notbold>137 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Feb 20th 12:14 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>/ooc on<br><br>The tapestry is disturbing not because of the content, which every broodling should be quite accustomed to, but due to the unusual hues woven into the fabric.&nbsp;&nbsp;Call it a bit of psychological warfare, if you will, since the guest would always be facing the tapestry when in conference with Usula.<br><br>/ooc off<br><br>Usula examined both of the documents Eiczk handed to her, and grumbled a curse directed at Glosk.<br><br><span style='color: green;'>&quot;As always, Eiczk, you are brave and honest in your questions and the voicing of your opinion.  However, the line between intelligent questions and impertinence is fine,<i> and you would do well not to cross it.</i>&quot;</span style='color: green;'>  Usula's voice indicated more than words the danger Eiczk had come close to with his words.  Nevertheless, Usula visibly calmed herself, <span style='color: green;'>&quot;I shall answer your questions.&quot;<br><br>&quot;Your father and mother were both sent to be killed for a very simple reason.  I cannot say I agree with the judgment, but I also cannot question the timeless wisdom involved.  Simply, your family wished to raise you.&quot;</span style='color: green;'>  Usula paused at Eiczk's startled expression.  <span style='color: green;'>&quot;Think about it, most intelligent one.  Can you name any in the Legion raised by their actual parents?  Can you think of any in the Brood who know who their parents are?  I tell you truth, young one, the Shaman make sure that the youth are raised by the society as a whole, not by individual parents.  True, we can take on the name of the clutch, and thus your surname of Draygoner, and I have taken the name Wurmbane.&quot;<br><br>&quot;Yes, we are both descended from families who have challenged dragons.  Further than this, I fear I do not know the answer you seek.  I do not know why Glosk targets your family, though nothing surprises me with that viper.  Perhaps your mother was a great necromancer, and that is the reason he had her killed.&quot;</span style='color: green;'>  Usula raised her eyes, <span style='color: green;'>&quot;Have you never noticed that there are no female members of the Brood of Kotiz in power, excepting myself?&quot;</span style='color: green;'>  <br><br>Eiczk blurted out &quot;Well, if what you imply is true, <b>HOW</b> are you alive?&quot;<br><br>Usula's eyes fogged for a moment before she responded.  <span style='color: green;'>&quot;I was taken far from Cabilis at the time when my power was developing, and by the time I returned, Glosk found he could not challenge me any longer.  Still, however, there are few females in the Brood of Kotiz.  Perhaps that is a fact due to the manipulations of the gods, I do not know.&quot;</span style='color: green;'>  Though Eiczk was intrigued, knowing there had to be more to the tale, he did not question Usula further.<br><br><span style='color: green;'>&quot;If you wish, I can look into the matter of your parents death further, and into the nature of your family name.&quot;</span style='color: green;'>  Eiczk nodded.<br><br><span style='color: green;'>&quot;In answer to your second question, I do not know what machinations that Harbinger Glosk has in store for your family.  He will not challenge me, however, and I would have you at my side.&quot;</span style='color: green;'>  Usula gave a non-committal shrug.  <span style='color: green;'>&quot;If you are asking what I want from you, well, the answer should be plain.  You are perhaps one of the most capable of the Legion, possessing not only great skill, but also an abiding intelligence that makes you more dangerous than your brothers.  Such a one can be a valuable ally in making Cabilis great once more.  I dream of Cabilis, Eiczk, and think you share the same dream.  If I did not think so, <i>you would be dead now</i>.&quot;</span style='color: green;'><br><br>Usula paused to take a sip from her drink.  Eiczk realized it was fruit juice.  He did not know why he found it strange, but now that he reflected on it, he had never seen Usula drink anything other than water or fruit juice, and for that matter, had never seen her eat anything but roots and vegetables (though she had served meat often enough).  Odd how such thoughts come to one at the most peculiar times.<br><br><span style='color: green;'>&quot;Your last question demonstrates what I mean.  Though I should have Prime Heirophant Vek killed for assuming to meddle in <b>MY</b> affairs, I suppose I shall drop that consideration, for now.  What do I plan to do <i>with Trakanon?  What do I plan to do with the dragons?</i>  Can you not guess by my surname?  I <b>am</b> Usula Wurmbane&quot;</span style='color: green;'> This was said in a haughty voice <span style='color: green;'>&quot;and I shall forever thirst after dragonblood.  They must be absolutely and utterly destroyed!&quot;</span style='color: green;'>  she responded to her own words with such venom that her eyes seemed to glow.<br><br><span style='color: green;'>&quot;I believe we are done here for the moment Legionnaire.  Wait here while I scribe a note to War Baron Eator, and then return to me on the morrow.&quot;</span style='color: green;'><br><br>Usula grabbed a parchment and a quill and began to write a letter<br><br><BLOCKQUOTE><b id=fs8>Quote:</b><hr size=1><br>Most Honorable War Baron Eator,<br><br>Greetings.  I have received your letter, good sir, and thank you for the use of Eiczk Draygoner as a liaison.  I honor you your activities, and look forward to your knowledge and wit in the Council.  Never, however, were you my puppet, dear Baron, and you would do well to remember that.  I have submitted myself to the will of the council, renouncing my station as Empress at the very height of my power, so do not presume to make demands of me, unless they are the unified demand of the council.<br><br>I ask that you turn over Legionnaire Eiczk to me, and choose one of the other two candidates to take over your position as you assume your place in the Council proper.  I ask this as a personal boon, in regard to our longstanding relationship, and do not demand this, though it is in my power to do so.  It is for the good of the Empire that I ask this, Eator.<br><br>Also, while military action is clearly under the control of the Council, my own actions as Enforcer of the Will of the Council are my own to dictate, as are the actions of those others I choose to recognize as Enforcers.  We are <i>above</i> the law of the council, though our whole existence shall be dedicated to the preservation of the will of the council and the good of the Iksar people as a whole.<br><br>Be well my old friend, and know I wish you no ill will.<br><br>Respectfully,<br><br>Usula Wurmbane, EWC<br><hr size=1></BLOCKQUOTE><br><br>Once Usula was done, she handed the folded note to Eiczk and dismissed him.  She still wondered about the black pearl she had gotten off the Lunarsa.  The Lunarsa said it had powerful enchantments, but this revelation of the dagger was something she had not expected.  She would have to ask the High Elf when she had the opportunity.<br><br>Putting those thoughts out of her mind for now, she composed another letter to Prime Heirophant Vex.<br><br><BLOCKQUOTE><b id=fs8>Quote:</b><hr size=1><br>Respected Vex,<br><br>If you value your position and if you value your life, do not presume to meddle in my affairs.  If ever rumor flies into my ear telling of your involvement in anything I have set aside for myself, you will die.<br><br>Know I speak truth in this Shaman.  I have dealt with enough of your interference in matters you do not understand.<br><br>Usula Wurmbane<br>Empress of Fear<br><hr size=1></BLOCKQUOTE><br><br>After sending off this message, she sought out Culris, to inquire if he knew anything in regards to the history of the Draygoner Brood.<br><br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed Feb 20 00:16:47 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br>Usula Wurmbane<br>Iksar Necromancer<br>Empress of Fear</td></tr>
