	   <tr><td colspan=2>It was during Pusbag's young teen years that he had his first significant experience with outsiders.&nbsp;&nbsp;Unkk and Pusbag had been playing with the skellies near the decrepit tower when they found themselves in a situation which overwhelmed their budding skills as magic users.  A giant water moccassin had bitten Pusbag after he and Unkk were slightly beat up from a nasty duel with a skeleton.  The snake had aggroed on the Trolls while fending off the skel's slashing sword.  Pusbag took a step backwards from the force of the blow and placed a foot on the normally placid viper's neck.  As soon as Pusbag's foot released the snake, it reared up and bit him three quick times in succession.<br><br>Unkk lopped off the head of the skeleton and proceeded to fend off the snake while Pusbag cast a series of heals on himself, but to no avail.  The poison was coursing through his veins weakening him to the point where he was becoming lightheaded.<br><br>All of a sudden, as darkness enveloped him he saw a glimpse of a young human woman's face and a soft cloth being placed on his wounds.  Within moments a large portion of his health returned, but the deadly venom was still knocking down his health.  Another bandage was administered to the bites.  More health returned.<br><br>Unkk had just finished off the snake and saw a hated foreigner-- a human! --bending over his best friend doing what for all he knew was inflicting a vicious wound that meant certain death to Pusbag.  As he screamed out in rage at the unexpected attack on his friend he raced over to assist Pusbag in repelling the invader.  In the blink of an eye he found himself on his back with his whole body numb and unable to move.  He blacked out shortly thereafter.<br><br>Angiisan moved back over to the hurting Troll.  She had no idea why she felt compelled to help a monster like this enormous Troll, but something inside her moved her hands to stop the poison from ending the life of the hideous creature.  She skillfully bound his wounds and nursed him back to the land of the living, all the while keeping him pinned to the ground by her knee.<br><br>For some mysterious reason, Pusbag was utterly at the mercy of the helpful woman since he was singularly unable to get to his feet.  However, that wasn't the only reason he remained still, she had an aura about her which calmed him, soothed him, and left him utterly content to lay on his back.  He lolled his head over and saw Unkk unconscious on the ground next to him.  &quot;Shhhhhh.  Your friend is fine-- just rest.  This poison will soon pass from your system and then you'll be free to go,&quot; he heard the woman quietly say.  As his strength returned, he slowly sat up.  The woman gracefully moved into a low crouch with one hand up in front of her body, the other poised to strike above her head.  Pusbag saw her foot lightly resting on its' toes in preparation to kick him under the chin and snap his head back.  He slowly showed her his empty palms to let her see he meant no harm when he realized she had spoken to him in his native tongue.  Amazed, he asked, &quot;<span style='color: green;'>Who are you?  And what are you doing here?  Why would you help me, a Troll?</span style='color: green;'>&quot;  <br><br>&quot;So many questions!&quot; she replied.  &quot;My name is Angiisan...&quot; and so one of the strangest episodes in Pusbag's life began as she explained what it was she was doing there in Innothule Swamp.<br><br>--Pusbag Infection<br>&nbsp;<br>Emperor and Shamanic High Priest of the Trolls<br>"Worship Innoruuk, you worthless cattle!"<br></td></tr>
