	   <tr><td colspan=2>When the danger had passed Angiisan explained to the two bewildered Trolls that she was in search of netted armor for the guild in Freeport, which loaned out various pieces to acolytes devoted to the Ashen Order of monks.&nbsp;&nbsp;She was a master in the secretive Order and had been sent out to procure some needed materials for the youngsters since there were few with her skills in martial arts and streetsmarts.<br><br>She had collected quite a few items and was heading back to her guild when she saw the commotion by the tower.  Knowing Da Swamp was filled with her species enemies, the Trolls, she had been careful not to attract the unwanted attention of the massive creatures while she harvested some Frogloks.  Yet when Angiisan had seen the plight of the hurting Trolls she felt some compassion and decided to intervene on their behalf.<br><br>Her bandaging skill saved Pusbag's life.  She always carried a large selection of aloe bandages (her favorites) and put them to use in healing the Troll's wounds.  If you asked her why she went out of her way to help a racial enemy she would have shrugged and told you it was an impulsive decision.  She was well known in her guild for thinking outside the box, which was also why she was a rising star in the Ashen Order.  An unconventional mind combined with deadly skill in unarmed combat made her a formidable foe.<br><br>&quot;Well, my two Trolls, where shall I begin?&quot; she asked.  &quot;Let me start at the beginning...&quot;<br><br>And with that she told her tale.  Trolls love a good story and sat raptly at attention as Angiisan wove an intricate plot of love, loss, and friendship.  And this is what she said...<br><br>*to be continued*<br><br>--Pusbag Infection<br>&nbsp;<br>Emperor and Shamanic High Priest of the Trolls<br>"Worship Innoruuk, you worthless cattle!"<br></td></tr>
