	   <tr><td colspan=2>&quot;I was born to a middle class merchant's family,&quot; Angiisan said, &quot;and led a normal childhood life for the most part.&nbsp;&nbsp;My parents were loving and in love, and took every opportunity to spend time together.  They doted on me and my siblings, yet were gently disciplining when we strayed too far from the rules they set out for us.  All in all it was a wonderful life we led in Freeport.  Father made a good living making and selling coats to rich and poor folks, Mother stayed at home and gave us a nurturing safe place to grow.<br><br>However, unlike my three brothers and two sisters, it seemed I was always seeing life from a different perspective.  Early on I was drawn to the martial arts with the high flying kicks, acrobatic leaps, and the lightning quick kata.  Every day after schooling I would be found haunting the yard in front of the Ashen Order watching the Masters in front practicing their craft.  I would try to follow them move for move, day in, day out, until the Guild Master called upon my parents one evening and asked to be given the opportunity to personally train me.  <br><br>He must have been convincing, because my parents called me into the kitchen and told me I was being given permission to join with the Order when I finished with my schooling.  I was to enter the guild as a novice and begin training as a monk!  <br><br>It was the best time of my life-- I was allowed to return home at night to my family after a long excitement-filled day of martial art training.  The Master exposed me to techniques that Grandmaster Bo had developed centuries earlier, methods which included staves, knives, chain, unarmed combat, and improvised weaponry.  Later, I was shown magical kata that involved disciplines in basic natural forces: stone, wind, water, light.  <br><br>The Master honed my innate abilities and expanded my repetoire, which in turn moved me up in the guild standings.  I was given special assignments which utilized the various techniques of sneaking, hiding, feigning death, among others.&quot;<br><br>*to be continued*<br>--Pusbag Infection<br>&nbsp;<br>Emperor and Shamanic High Priest of the Trolls<br>"Worship Innoruuk, you worthless cattle!"<br></td></tr>
