	   <tr><td colspan=2>/ooc sorry this one is so long, but I got to writing, and just couldn't stop. I hope everyone enjoys this. and for those monty python fans, please excuse the inclusion of a line from the quest for the Holy Grail. I was watching it while writing this. And on a side note.. the depection of the fall of sebilis does not really make Eiczk uncomfortable, as you will soon see. its the possibility of a recurrance of that event that does. No biggie, just so you know. /ooc off<br><br>Two Iksar stood by the water's edge, both with swords in hand. One old, One young. Side by side they stood still as statues. Each was stripped to the waist, Their armor set aside. Without warning both moved in unison, swinging their blades in a tight arc, then reversing it and swinging upwards. Again they stood still. Their blades stood at ready, out perpendicular to their bodies, both hands on the hilt. They both spun to the left, and swung in a wide arc, a blow that would decapitate any bipedal being of their size. Again stillness came. &quot;Ready the blades!&quot; called the old one. &quot;The blades are ready.&quot; answered the young. They both begain striking and dodging, moving through various sword strikes and ripostes. All the while in unison with the other. To them time moved like a river over flat ground: Slow and even. To others watching it would seem a whirlwind of movement and color. Just as quickly as they began, they stopped. Blades were again at the ready. &quot;Sheathe your honor, young one.&quot; said the Elder. Both closed their stance bringing legs together, swords moved from the ready position as the two slid them into their scabbards. The old and the young both stood upright, hand on hilt, staring towards the water. as one the two intoned: &quot;<I><span style='color: green;'>May fear guide our spirit and our blades. Honor to the fallen in combat, death to those who fail in it. For Sebilis, our honor is always ready.</span style='color: green;'></I>&quot; An old saying brought new again. An old warrior raising the new.<br><br>&quot;Do you know what you ended up standing in?&quot; the younger one said with a smile. &quot;Oh shut up Eiczk. I know all bloody well what I am in. If I ever find the Burynai that left this, I will have a new pelt to hang on my wall.&quot; <br><br>War Baron Eator was an older Iksar, tall lithe and scarred heavily. He moved off of the mess, scraping his foot through the sand. Eiczk just laughed. &quot;Well old friend perhaps if you had watched your turnings instead of that bird up on the ledge, you would have spaced yourself to avoid ... putting your foot in it, shall I say?&quot; With a growl Eator moved off towards the gulley that led back up to the remainder of the Field of Bone.&quot;I can't help it.. I'm hungry.&quot; The younger iksar grabbed their armor and walked along side him. &quot;M'lord, I thank you for practicing with me. It was enjoyable as always.&quot; <br><br>&quot;Must you always be so formal all the time, hatchling? as if we had not known each other for many years now. I could count on one hand the number of times you have slipped and called me old friend. Perhaps even minus a few fingers.&quot; Replied the War Baron. Eiczk sighed, casting his eyes downards. &quot;Yes, sire, it must be. You are the War Baron of Cabilis, leader of the Legion. I am a Legionnaire. Though we are friends as well, I still owe you the respect of your rank.&quot; He smiled. &quot;Very well you young whelp one day I'll get you to relax some, now lets head back. There are papers on my desk I have to dig through and sign. I would sooner face the Troll army than that, but it must be done.&quot; <br><br>The two walked up into the field, circumventing the pit, as it was shorter. A lone skeleton came running in their direction. &quot;Oh boy, more practice.. looks like those papers get to wait.&quot; Said the Baron excitedly as he unsheathed his sword. The younger stayed his hand seeing something the elder did not. Eiczk had been known to have very sharp eyes. &quot;No that is not a skelton from the pit. That is a servant of a necromancer. Looks like one of us is needed.&quot; The skeleton stopped and began chittering away as if they could understand. How they made that noise without any larynx was till a boggle to both. Since both looked at the creatured with confused stares, the skeleton grabbed Eickz's arm, and pulled him. Eiczk slid his sword out of its sheath, swinging upwards and removing the skeletons arm. The cadaver stared at the bones on the ground. With his blade held high, he spun backwards, bringing the blade around with considerable force. Force that severed the head of the skeleton, and released the incantations that held it to the mortal plane. &quot;Well it looks like we know who is summoned, M'lord. I do so believe you have those papers to sign, and I have to go see Usula.&quot; The War Baron nodded and started off to cabilis. A group of Partisans that had been standing on the ledge above the ocean formed up on the War Baron as escort. The War Baron began lecturing them on the forms he and Legionnaire Draygoner were using. Eiczk dashed off ahead of them.<br><br>Arriving back in fortress Talishan, Eiczk stopped momentarily to grab some bloodwater to cool himself. He also removed a small bundle from his quarters. A calm feeling had come over him. Of all the things he enjoyed doing, He loved practicing with Eator. Even if it was to train recruits. The baron had sort of taken him in when his father and mother were killed. At the time he was only 7. To Eiczk, though he remembered his father, It was Eator whom he believed took the role. When he arrived In the Tower of Death. Usula was waiting.<br><br>Her question was like striking a brick wall. Very uncomfortable. He had come to ask questions given the light of the most recent events, but had not expected this. Despite the discomfort, he maintained a cold expression. &quot;First Usula there are things you must know, if you do not know them already.&quot; He removed his sword, Laying it upon the ground. It was a long sword, Blade almost as thick as the Quilions, tapered to a sharp point. The blade appeared as metal, but somehow seemed harder. Upon the hilt was a large black scale. Usula had seen this blade before. Along with the two Ykeshen short swords tucked behind his belt, this comprised part of the arsenal of weapons he mainly used. &quot;This blade has been in my family since after the fall of Rile. It has passed from father to son down countless generations. Before Rile we were slaves to the evil of Venril Sathir. Taken from the Jarsath tribe and forced to work in the forges that founded Sebilis. After Sathir fell, and Rile became Emperor, we were freed. He gave us a name... Sh'ethok. Translated from the ancient language of the Soriz.. Forge Keepers. We stayed in service of Rile, and forged the armors and weapons that would eventually be used during the war against the Dragons. We were however still considered slaves, and were not allowed to serve in any of the guilds. <br><br>The Sebilisan people laughed at us, tormented us and slew our children out of spite. Then came the day that Rile died. His ship was beset and destroyed in a storm conjured by the dragons. Many were angry and wanted blood for his death. All they seemed to do was add their own to the mettle. One of my ancestors cared for Rile, and felt that his death would not go unanswered. He took a blade and led the sons of Sh'ethok out upon the battlefield. He was the eldest of my family. Many warriors laughed at them, some tried to scare them off. Unabated, they attacked the dragons as if Thule himself drove them. Of the 30 dragons that were there that day, only 2 left living. Not one of the Sh'ethok died. They swore to defend Sebilis until not one Dragon yet lived. That still stands today. Atrebe, Rile's son finally allowed them into the Warrior's guild. It was not long before many were leading our troops against the dragons. My Grandsire took that day a mighty claw and a scale from one of the fallen dragons.&quot; Eiczk touched the blade lightly, and it seemed to glow softly. &quot;He forged them both into this blade. My grandsire's name was Eiczk Sh'ethok, we just call him the Sh'ethok. <br><br>As my family grew in fame people began to fear them, and called them The Dragonslayers. Not one of my kin has ever fallen in combat against a dragon. They have all wielded this blade. After Sebilis fell and our people were scattered the meaning of the dragonslayers was lost. Soon the name was truncated to what we know today. Draygoner. This happened many many generations ago, and only the first born of our family is taught its history. My mother did not know the history back to Sh'ethok's day until later in my life. On my naming day, my father was out scouting and was not present to name me. My mother chose my name without any knowledge of its past. I am also not first born. I had an elder brother, of whom I will not speak. It is, however, enough to say that he no longer lives. <br><br><br>Even though my brother died after my father, My father taught me the history. I am the first to break our history, my mother said. None were to ever be named after our grandsire. I am. Only the firstborn are to know the history of our family. I am Secondborn. The sword of the Sh'ethok must be passed from Father to Firsborn Son. I took this blade from my brother's hands after he was killed.&quot; <br><br>Usula took all of this in like a sponge. &quot;This is most interesting, but what does it have to do with anything you wish to know?&quot;<br><br>Eiczk smiled. &quot;Quite simply, I have broken almost every tradition in our family. I intend to keep it that way. There is another tradition my family has, one I do not like. From father to son this blade has passed. The blade is passed when the Firstborn recieves his summons to the Guild appropriate for his abilities. For my brother that was from the Crusaders. In every generation back to the day of Sh'ethok, within a month of the sword being passed on, the Father is killed somehow. Also each generation, the mother disappears or dies at the same time. Not a single Draygoner has taken a wife that was not a necromancer. My mother and father were killed by a Giant Ambush in the Frontier Mountains. They had been told that the giants were fleeing the mountains, and to investigate the cause. When they arrived apparently the Giants were actually mounting an assault force. The gathering was well known by the guilds in Cabilis, but not informed to my parents.&quot; Eiczk reached behind him and pulled out the small package he brought with him. Out of it he pulled a dagger and old parchment. The dagger he laid beside his sword. The scroll he read aloud. <br>_________________________________<br><i><br>&quot;War Baron Eator<br>Fortress Talishan<br><br>Greetings to you Noble Eator,<br><br>I am writing to you to inform you of a joint venture between our guilds. As you know Trooper Draygoner has a wife within our guild. Since we have need of recon to the Frontier mountains you are to send Trooper Draygoner there post haste. Do not inform him of his mission. that I will leave to our representative His wife will acompany him as our representative.<br><br>I also reccomend you begin training his replacement as I feel that he will be moving on to better things after this assignment. This is not a request Eator, I cannot stress the urgency of this assignment.&quot; </i><br>_________________________________<br><br>He finished reading and looked at Usula. &quot;It is signed Harbinger Glosk.&quot; He tossed the paper at her feet. He then picked up the dagger. Upon the dagger's hilt there was a setting for some gem, but the gem appeared to be missing. &quot;This was given to my mother before they left. As you know we have Giants captive within the city repairing some of the damage they once caused.&quot; Eiczk pulled from the bag a small black pearl and placed it in the hilt of the dagger. The hilt looked identical to the ring Usula had given him. Immediately the dagger began to vibrate and emit a loud high pitched squeal. Soon the sound was intolerable and painful. The iksar removed the pearl, and the sound stopped. &quot;I have found that this dagger does this when within 10 metres of a Giant. There is a giant outside working on the tower at this minute. Harbinger Glosk gave this to my mother personally. From research I have done here in the tower it looks that the brood has had every male of my line killed back to the days of Rile. So what is it I want to know?&quot; Eiczk held up a finger &quot;One, why did the brood have my mother and father killed,&quot; Raising another finger, &quot;Two what does the brood intend of me, being of the Draygoner line, &quot; a third finger raised, &quot;and Three, what is it you wish of Trakanon?&quot; Usula looked shocked at him.<br><br>&quot;Ahh you see those books you had are very old. I am not a magic user, but I know the scripts used in Necromantic and Shamanistic practices. After all we have both guilds here, my mother was a Necromancer, and my little sister is a shaman. I will not disclose her name to you as I fear for her safety. Those books are neither. I have a good memory Usula, and remembered some of the script. Some Questions posed to the shaman proved most interesting. The script is Elder Elvish, and parts of it are Dragon speech as well. The names of the books were Mind Wrack and Essence of Sorcery according to Prime Hierophant Vek. He could be wrong. his dragon was rusty. He did mention that from what he heard of them, both books were in studies of draining mystical energy. Last time I checked we only have one foe that requres that potentency of magic, namely Trakanon and his friends. So, Usula I request that you answer these questions three. I would hate to see you become another Dag and be slain for studying forbidden arts. I also warn you, Dragons are my family's mortal foe. Ally yourself with them in any way and you make a foe of me. I must beg your forgiveness I almost forgot. I have something for you.&quot; He pulled a small parchment out of his armor, and handed it to her. it read as follows:<br>_________________________________<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<i>To Council Member Usula<br>  Tower of Death.<br><br>  Usula, <br><br>  It has come to my attention that as of late you have been using the Legion of Cabilis to further the goals of our empire. I applaud you and encourage you to continue. However, from this day forward any requests of military action must be approved by the council as a whole, not upon a whim of yours. I assign you as a Liaison, Legionnaire Eiczk Draygoner. If you have military requests Let him know as he represents the will of the Legion. I have notified Glox of this, and he has aggreed that military action will be decided in full council. <br><br>               <b>We will not be puppets anymore.</b><br><br>May Cazic grant you victory, <br><br>War Baron Eator</i><br>_________________________________<br><br>Fury seemed to roll off Usula in waves.<br><br>&quot;I trust that Eator was quite implicit in his instructions? Know this Usula, I do still serve you because your interests serve Cabilis, and because I like you. Eator will soon be too old to lead, and will be stepping down. I am one of three other candidates for that position. Though it would pain me to see you opposed, if you do take path with dragons in anyway, the legion will stand behind me against you. I ask that you answer me in truth now, I will not hate you for your interest in the dragons. Neither will I seek action against you so long as answer my questions with Honor and sincerity. <br><br>The Legionnaire waited patiently for her answer.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Tue Feb 19 01:32:31 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br>Eiczk Draygoner<br>34th rank Warrior<br>Legionnaire of Cabilis<br>Xegony<br><i>-Death comes to all, but for the fallen it shall come with a vengance.</i></td></tr>
