	   <tr><td colspan=2>Pusbag ground his teeth as he fought the powerful geas with every fiber of his being.&nbsp;&nbsp;He strained and struggled to assert authority over his limbs, but to no avail.  Hard as he tried he could not regain control over his body.  His mind was open and conscious of what was occuring, but helpless to prevent the puppeteer from pulling on the strings and making him dance.<br><br>This was a challenge he had never faced before and as yet, had no answer for the powerful enchantments which held him in thrall to the Iksar.  As they traveled across Kunark Pusbag continued to fruitlessly fight the magic suppressing his will.<br><br>The Troll had an inkling of what was in store for him once he had been commanded to pick up his weapons and armor and set out with his master.  The direction they walked was a straight shot towards a certain fight.  He knew beyond a shadow of a doubt he was to employ those formidable combat skills he had spent a lifetime honing to effect the deaths of this lizard enchanter's enemies.<br><br>Pusbag became despondent at the sheer helplessness he felt.  It was like watching another person from the vantage point of their own eyes.  Well, he had no choice but to wait out the spell and grab whatever opportunities came his way to decide his own fate.  But in the meantime, he was at the beck and call of his master.<br><br>--Pusbag Infection <br>&nbsp;<br>Emperor and Shamanic High Priest of the Trolls<br>"Worship Innoruuk, you worthless cattle!"<br></td></tr>
