	   <tr><td colspan=2>Unbeknownst to Eizck, Usula was doing nothing so much as marking the leaders of the Tier Dal.&nbsp;&nbsp;It would be impossible for her to approach their queen, but the marking of the prominent leaders of the various guilds was much less complicated as they were not so well protected.  The Tier Dal were more arrogant than the Iksar, and Usula counted that a weakness.  After all, the Tier Dal would never expect two Iksar to come to their lands, and especially not to come to the very heart of their abode.<br><br><span style='color: green;'>&quot;Wait here&quot;</span style='color: green;'> Usula said to the legionnaire <span style='color: green;'>&quot;and continue to read.  Do not respond to anything or anyone until I return.  Oh&quot;</span style='color: green;'> she continued as if an afterthought <span style='color: green;'>&quot;Be prepared to run.&quot;</span style='color: green;'><br><br>Usula cloaked herself in shadow and entered into the complex housing the Necromancers and Shadow Knights of the Tier Dal.  Inside the building, she noted the power of the guild leaders.  It seemed, by the traffic within the complex, that the Tier Dal had many who followed the dark paths.  Many more than the Iksar, at any rate.  Still, she was extremely aware of the limitations of magic.  Hidden as she was, she exited the complex and entered into the great library of Neriak.  There, she took several interesting books from the walls and placed them into her sack.  She had what she came for.  Unfortunately for the Tier Dal who happened to be in the library the same time she was there, they found only the comforting arms of Innoruuk waiting for them after their death.<br><br>Eizck gave a small start when Usula suddenly placed her hand on his shoulder from behind.  He did not flinch, much to his credit.  <span style='color: green;'>&quot;Time for us to return to Cabilis, Eizck.  I think we have found what we needed.  Still, we would not want the Tier Dal to be too comfortable in their city, now would we?  We must be off.&quot;</span style='color: green;'><br><br>Eizck did not respond.  Then he heard the shouting.  If nothing else, the Tier Dal were quick, and guards were rushing to the Library.  Eizck, remembering some of his battles in the Overthere, did not think he would like to stick around much longer.<br><br>They made it to the entrance before they were discovered.  Apparently, Usula did not care for sulking.  She cast aside her robes, hissed loudly, and <b><span style='color: red;'>destroyed</b></span style='color: red;'> the guard at the left side of the entrance.  The guard at the right responded quickly.<br><br>Fortunately for Usula, Eizck responded just as quickly and engaged the guard.  Usula cackled as she began a dark enchantment, summoning an undead servant to her cause.  The dark boned assassin backstabbed the hapless Dragoon, and Eizck finished him off.  Nevertheless, the battle caused several other Tier Dal to rush out.  Usula sent her pet at them, but as it was specifically crafted for assassination, it did not stand long against the combined might of the now stirred up Tier Dal.  <br><br>Usula, laughing the entire time, called for Eizck to follow her as she set off at a run, heading south.  Sounds of pursuit were clearly evident, but Usula continued to laugh.  Eizck ran quietly and with determination, rather surprised that Usula had the endurance to run such a distance without tiring.  Then again, he thought, she does not have much by way of armor, either.<br><br>After a while, they reached a structure that was becoming rather familiar to Eizck, and he was not surprised to see the Lunarsa sorceress standing at the pinnacle of the structure.<br><br>Still, there was someone standing between the two Iksar and the High Elf.  It was a Tier Dal, and well equipped at that.  Eizck immediately engaged the elf.  The battle was furious, as the elf was quite skilled with the sharp edged weapon he carried.  Eizck thrust, but the elf countered.  The elf lunged, and Eizck riposted.  The battle went on for only thirty seconds or so, but to Eizck it seemed hours.  Finally, he was able to lunge and deliver a deathblow to the elf.  Then it was that the noticed he was injured, and rather severely at that.  Knowing that pursuit was close behind, he joined Usula and the Lunarsa upon the platform.<br><br><br>Both he and Usula were standing in the Dreadlands, near the ruins of the old Combine Empire a moment later.  The Lunarsa was nowhere to be seen.<br><br>Sighing, Usula cast a spell, and in doing so, groaned a bit.  Eizck saw his wounds disappear at a rapid rate, much more rapid than his natural regeneration would normally allow.<br><br><span style='color: green;'>&quot;Why must I waste my time casting such a spell upon you Eizck?&quot;</span style='color: green;'> Usula asked hauntingly.  He had no reply.  Usula then reached into her sack and pulled out a ring.  Handing it to Eizck, she said <span style='color: green;'>&quot;Here, perhaps this shall make you a bit less likely to be so easily injured.  I will not abide injured servants.&quot;</span style='color: green;'><br><br>Eizck looked at the ring.  It was a black pearl velium ring, and imbued with a magical essence.  Eizck had not seen it's like before, and was amazed.<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Usula Wurmbane<br>Iksar Necromancer<br>Empress of Fear</td></tr>
