<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101400605218424></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101400605218424><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=journal.html?user=2076&mid=101400605218424>RE: Incursion Part II</a> <a id=fs8 href=journal.html?user=2076&mid=101400605218424#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=113679><span id=Sage>Eiczk</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>20 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Feb 17th 11:21 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>The Dreadlands. A place Eiczk hated. Covered in ice, crawling with Vermin, it was not his most favorite of places. He was still glad to be back from his journey. The twinge along his side was subsiding as he healed, but the fury inside was not abating. The woman was crazy. He so much wanted to ask Usula if she liked stirring up wasps nests as a child. He also wondered if she remembered the stings. He had taken her across the continent of Antonica for what... <b><span style='color: red;'>BOOKS!</span style='color: red;'></b> Then she commented on her having to heal him constantly. &quot;I wonder how she would do against a Tier'Dal Blademaster.&quot; he thought . He had only fought a few of the softskins, but that one was no apprentice, nor was he a common guard. That Eiczk had only received a gash across his flank was by the will of Cazic. Granted he had enjoyed the fight. However he was so busy worrying about anyone attacking Usula, that he failed to realize the enjoyment. At least she had enjoyed it, he could still hear her laughing.<br><br>The Iksar looked at the ring she had just given him. It was a beautiful Black pearl, set within velium. He had seen such rings before, they were supposed to aid in your speed. This one looked slightly different. At first he had wanted to throw the ring at her and tell her what she could do with it. Instead he pocketed it. &quot;I will make sure to use this as needed,... my lady.&quot; This last he added with a questioning tone, as if to question the worth of her title. He bowed stiffly, and coldly stalked down the Spire. How she could get under his scales so easily now was a puzzle that made Eiczk's head hurt. Since he had all but declared for her, he was tied to her surely as stink on a troll.<br><br>He drew his sword and started towards the tunnel that lead out into the frozen wastes. Usula followed. As they walked he thought through things. <br><br>&quot;She takes us to the den of foul sofskins for books. Why? I don't recognize those books. She also was gone much too long to have just gotten those and come back. What else had she done? We also go quietly along allowing no one to see us. Then we break out of the city killing guards and Thule knows what else she killed in Iksar style, as if to paint a sign. She wants everyone to know who was in Neriak, and that we possess those books. Those books hold import, and I hope they were worth the risk.&quot; Eiczk sighed. He was not one for puzzling out the machinations of a necromancer. He understood combat, not politics.<br><br>Usula seemed to glare at him, such that he could feel it with his back turned. It would be a long journey home.<br><br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Sun Feb 17 23:25:47 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br>Eiczk Draygoner<br>34th rank Warrior<br>Legionnaire of Cabilis<br>Xegony<br><i>-Death comes to all, but for the fallen it shall come with a vengance.</i></td></tr>
