	   <tr><td colspan=2>The small gnome sat quietly behind a rock watching the two iksars converse before the robed one cast a spell and faded from view.&nbsp;&nbsp;Not daring to speak to cast the spell which would make the Necromancer visible to him.  He waited quietly wondering why he had taken all the precautions of following these Iksar all the way from the desert, almost always cloaked with the invisiblity that his art granted him.  <br><br>He knew only two things: These Iksar were obviously important, and they MUST have had something to do with the death of his uncle.<br><br>A tear came to his eye as the thoughts of his Uncle Attalon came to mind.  He quickly pulled himself together, realizing much time had passed as he thought to himself. He heard a soft sound to his left and turning quickly, he saw nothing.  He sat confused for a moment before he realized that something was there, only cloaked with magic. He crouched lower behind his rock, knowing that he was no match for these two Iksar yet, and wondering again why he followed them. The noise's source became apparent as the robed Iksar appeared behind the armored one and said it was time to go. The Iksar left the city with a large comotion, the little gnome slipping past as teh Robed Iksar destroyed a Dark Elf by sheer force of will. The gnome was suddenly very glad he hadn't attempted any reckless attacks.  The Iksar took off in a run, the Tier'Dal momentarily distracted by a skeletal pet the Iksar had conjured. The gnome ran as fast as he could after the Iksar, again wondering why he was following the Lizards. He could not keep up with them as his legs were much shorter than theirs. He began to perspire as he ran on, his eyes closed wishing again and again he hadn't left the safety of Ak'Kanon(sp?). He suddenly tripped over something and landed face down in dirt.  He cursed quietly as he looked to see what is was that he had tripped over.  A black tome marked with a skull on the cover lay on the ground.  <br><br>&quot;That damn Iksar must have dropped this.&quot;<br><br>He was about to toss the book as he happened to glace at the binding of the book.  Tier'dal runes covered the binding.  <br><br>&quot;Huh? She must have stolen this... hmmmm...&quot;<br><br>He heard footsteps behind him as he stood up, and began to panic before he realized his Invisiblity was still working. He looked around then cast the Gate spell which would bring his to the relative safety of the Oasis in Ro.  A flash of mana and the Gnome and book disappeared.<br><br> Azuthe (Name Pending)<br> Gnome Necromancer <br> 23rd Circle of the Dark Arts<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
