<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101397828817135></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101397828817135><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=journal.html?user=2076&mid=101397828817135>Incursion part 1-A Soldier and the Elves?</a> <a id=fs8 href=journal.html?user=2076&mid=101397828817135#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=113679><span id=Sage>Eiczk</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>20 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Feb 17th 3:38 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>A cold breeze blew through the Nektulos Forest. The trees swayed in the breeze, as if dancing to an unknown piper's tune. Eiczk wondered who the piper was, and if he was also dancing to that same tune. He sat on the edge of a small camp, munching on his favorite snack... Vein worms. Sleeping not far away was Usula, Council Member of New Sebilis. They had been traveling for some time through the wilds of Antonica. Since Freeport and the surrounding areas were under constant watch, he had led Usula through the Rathe Mountains, and up through Lake Rathetear. It had been an arduous journey, of which he was not sure why they were making it. It took them a week to finally arrive at their destination. High Hold Pass was not the best of locations for Iksar to sneak through unnoticed. In fact one guard had seen them, but did not live long enough to give alarm. He also increased the few meager rations Eiczk had brought by a factor of 10.<br><br>The two had come from Kunark upon one of the new Naval ships that were built. They moved fast, and were not rickety like that old barge that used to run from Timorous Deep to the Overthere. When they were underway Usula had informed him this was a recon mission into Tier'Dal Territory. &quot;Those lands are dangerous, even for one of your great power.&quot; He had warned. However she did not listen. Her plans were to penetrate the Third Gate of Neriak for some purpose. The Third Gate was about as far into Neriak as one could get. It also was home to the Necromancer, Cleric and ShadowKnight guilds. The oddest part was why it was they who had to come. A Member of the new council and a Legionnaire of Cabilis; to what end did this serve? Soldiers and Troopers usually did recon missions. If it evolved dealing with Magic, the Brood or The Scaled Mystics were involved. So why did they have to come? He cared not that it was risky, but the logic of it escaped him. <i><b>Any incursions into hostile territory with high-ranking officers or members of the court are to be escorted by a minimum of 30 warriors and 10 Shaman or Necromancers.</b></i> This was the rule set forth concerning officials. Granted this would have to be changed as it was made during the times of the Empress, but it still stood as a rule of the Legion. &quot;So what is so important that others cannot be trusted with this task.&quot; He shrugged. &quot;I don't think I really want to know&quot;, Eiczk thought.<br><br>Now they sat encamped not too far from the outer gates of Neriak. He was on guard, as was Usula's Minion that had come with her. The young warrior lifted his head, smelling the air. It feels so much like being inside a spell, He thought. The air did seem to have an energy to it, none of which felt good. The other eerie part was the sounds of the forest, or lack there of. Breezes blew occasionally bringing cold drafts along with it. They also stirred the trees. He could hear them creak as they swayed. However, that was all he could hear. No birds, no sounds of any other animal that moved. Eiczk really did not like this place. *SNAP!* It was the only warning the warrior received that someone was within a few paces of their camp. Wasting no movement, Eiczk brought up his bow, and loosed an arrow. It flew true, right into the eye socket of a Dark-Elf. The elf spun around from the force of the impact, then collapsed to the ground in a bloody lump. Not moving, the Iksar listened for any other sounds nearby. Silence answered him coldly. The soon-to-be-food was dressed in a very dingy robe, which looked as if it had been stored folded for some time. &quot;An initiate of some kind, nothing more than a child!&quot; he thought out loud. <br><br>&quot;Yes, a child. One of their new Necromancers.&quot; Echoed a voice behind him.<br><br>&quot;You are awake, my lady. It appears Cazic has seen fit to send us more rations. Though I would rather he sends more Vein Worms.&quot; The lizard grinned devilishly. Shouts came from the northeast, screams and the sound of metal on metal. &quot;Combat!&quot; Eiczk cried. His hand went to his sword loosing it for battle. <br><br>&quot;No my friend, we go not to battle now. It is time for us to be silent. We must journey to the city now. I have been waiting for this.&quot;<br><br>Usula stood and began casting some dark magic. The now decedent body was engulfed in some strange noxious fire. After the flames cleared only a spot of char remained. They stole away, creeping towards the Gates of Neriak. It did not take long to get there. A long tunnel carved into the side of the mountain marked the entrance to the Tier'Dal fortress. Normally it would be Flanked by guards, and supported by others scouting nearby. There were no guards. &quot;Odd.&quot;, mumbled the warrior.<br><br>&quot;This is where we part company, I did not ask you to come in with me, as it gets dangerous from here.&quot; <br><br>Eiczk looked at her, and responded in kind. &quot;Over my dead body! I am not letting you go in there without some protection. No matter how great your power is, their numbers alone say you will die if you go alone. I will follow you if it means going into the heart of Freeport Naked! You cannot die, as Royalty... err I mean as Council members are more important than any member of the Legion. We may die that you shall lead us.&quot; He still was getting used to the fact that Usula was no longer the Empress.<br><br>&quot;Very well, here then.&quot; Usula pulled 2 large cloaks out from the pack her pet was carrying, and tossed one to him. &quot;This will make travel easier through the gates. And crouch down some, remember we are larger than these softskins, we will be questioned if we do not appear as Tier'Dal.&quot; <br><br>Eiczk nodded to this put on the cloak and ducked down to what he believed to be the height of a sofskin elf. The cloaks covered every inch of their scales, and the hoods were deep enough to hide their facial features in shadow. They strode into the city, Usula just behind the Warrior. <br><br>It did not take long before they were passing the dark-skins. Legionnaire Draygoner found it hard not to out sword and carve a way to safer ground. As they passed amazingly most just nodded to them. They were not questioned. It did not take long to reach the third gate, though many times they had to step aside to prevent from being run over by guards. They all seemed to be running towards the gates. Pity he could not understand what half of them were saying. Only a few used Dark Speech. Usula led them to a large building that looked like the jaws of a great beast. she pulled him aside, and sat down, handing him a book. <br><br>&quot;Look like you are studying it.&quot; Usula whispered.<br><br>Eiczk complied. keeping the hood of his cloak down, he began reading over the book. With the long sleeves covering his hands, it was difficult, but he did manage. It was comprised of symbols and words the Iksar had never seen before. As he studied the book, he kept looking around trying to see if anyone noticed them. The softskins around him just walked by hardly giving them a glance. The common occurrence of cloaked figures studying in the dark worked as an excellent guise. <br><br>&quot;What now, my lady?&quot; the warrior inquired.<br><br>Usula smiled a knowing smile, and replied:<br>&quot;Now we wait for the fun to begin.&quot;<br><br>Eiczk felt that this was going to be a long, bad day.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Sun Feb 17 17:30:52 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br>Eiczk Draygoner<br>34th rank Warrior<br>Legionnaire of Cabilis<br>Xegony<br><i>-Death comes to all, but for the fallen it shall come with a vengance.</i></td></tr>
