<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101391891414102></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101391891414102><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=journal.html?user=2076&mid=101391891414102>Pusbag and the Geas</a> <a id=fs8 href=journal.html?user=2076&mid=101391891414102#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=60669><span id=Guru>Mugali the Mighty</span></a>, <span id=Guru>Guru</span><br><span id=notbold>400 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Feb 16th 11:08 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Pusbag looked up from his mumblings and rantings.&nbsp;&nbsp;Icewind Novastorm stood before him.  Behind Icewind was the usual collection of Dwarven guards, weapons sprouting off of their hearty frames in all directions.<br><br>Pusbag gave Icewind a great toothy smile,&quot;So old friend, have you come to gloat?  While you enjoy yourself, perhaps you could give me some food?&quot;.<br><br>Icewind said nothing, then began to cast a spell.  Pusbag was no intiate, he was well schooled in all manners of spell casting.  Yet, these were Koada'dal words he had never heard spoken before.  He stared at the High Elf and growled.  His eyes became heavy, and he fell asleep, completely oblivious to what was happening.<br><br><br>___________________________________<br><br><br><br>The former Troll King awoke.  The sun glared down from above.  Wherever I am, thought Pusbag, it is high noon.  He sat up, and noticed suddenly that he was in full armor.  A great iron mace lay on the ground before him.  He stood and picked it up.  It weighed at least fifty stones.  It wasn't his beloved sceptre, but, it would do.  It had powerful magics in it, he would have to discover what they were.<br><br>Pusbag turned and looked to the horizon.  He recognized this place.  He was in the Dreadlands of Kunark.  How he came here he would very much like to know.  A tall Iksar stepped from the underbrush to his left.<br><br>&quot;Ahh, you are awake Troll, good!  It is time for us to begin our journey.&quot;  The Iksar picked up a bag from the ground and began to walk away.  In his right hand was a long gnarled staff.  Pusbag had no intention of doing anything the Iksar said, yet, he was completely within the creature's will.  Briefly, he fought with every ounce of his will, then succumbed to the desire of the lizard man.  Pusbag knew from that moment on he would have to protect and follow the Iksar where ever this adventure led.  He could not fight the geas, the great quest placed upon him.<br><br>&quot;Where are we going friend?  I am famished.&quot;, Pusbag blurted out as he set after the Iksar.  <br><br>The Iksar stopped and turned around,&quot;Here, I will make us invisible, then you won't be so hungry.  When night comes we will hunt up a feast.&quot;  The Iksar cast a some spells, rendering both of the travelers invisible.  Pusbag was curious, he hadn't known the Iksar to cast such invisibility spells. <br><br>&quot;Who are you? Where are we going?,&quot; he asked again as they set out.<br><br>Without looking back, the Iksar said,&quot;You know of me Troll, for now you may call me Gezz.  Where are we going?,&quot; the Iksar began to laugh,&quot;Why, we are going to speak with a Dragon of course!&quot;<br><br>Ironhom Hammerforge<br>Dwarven Paladin<br>Tallon Zek Server<br>&nbsp;<br>Judd Jaggedoak <br>(deceased)<br>Wood Elf Ranger<br><br><br><br><br></td></tr>
