	   <tr><td colspan=2>With the Three under his command, and in his new, but still scarred state, Culris began his diversion for the Tier'Dal.<br>Although he saw his queen as greedy, and liable to fall as the Shissar and the first Sebilisian empire had, he none the less carried out what he was asked. He knew that certain things could be done to save those who mattered, but first to matters at hand.<br>He proceeded from his hidden chambers to the Haggle Baron's. There, hidden away in a room of his own construction was something that would destroy the already shakey alliance with the Koada and Fier'Dal. What he had was caught in the Dreadlands, killing iksar knights and mystics, cutting them down one by one, till Culris came, and defeated it in a glorious battle, that only he and the... thing... were the survivors of. What he had was a Koada'Dal Evoker, a dangerous female indeed, and only with a power protection around the room was Culris able to enstill her. However, she was sudued, and imprisoned for many seasons now, but if knowledge of her came out to the Lunsara or the Icewind, the alliance would be broken.<br>As he entered the room, the Koada'Dal acknowledged him, one artist of magic to another. Addressing her in that of a Elf, though rather shakily, he relayed the story of why he had been absent of late, and developments over Norrath, though she was a prisoner, Culris was not an unreasonable jailer, and kept her informed of events, well-fed and provided items for experiments, but he knew not to be so lax, for she still pined for the Faydark.<br>Then he came to the matter of the Tier'Dal, and noticed that the elf became agiated when their name was spoken. This would aid him much he thought.<br><br>&quot;How would you like to help iksar?&quot;<br>&quot;I will not aid you, you treat me well, but i am still imprisoned&quot;<br>&quot;very well, but help against... black?...elves?&quot;<br>&quot;If i can help destroy them, then i will, the fallen must be saved, and only death can realse them&quot;<br>&quot;Then help me...&quot;<br><br>With this Culris produced a vial, and the Visceral Dagger, used only in incantations of upmost importance<br><br>&quot;Give wrist white elf&quot; Culris commanded<br>As the wrist was produced, he quickly sliced it open, and captured the blue blood of the Koada'Dal into the vial, until it spilled over. Thn he corked the vial back up, and secreated it about his person and went to the door. The elf was writhing on the floor, apparently losing blood was hurtful, and she could not regenrate skin and flesh where the wound had been. Such was the weakness of all those who were not the children of Cazic-Thule.<br>With a quick movement of his clawed hands, he exchanged wounds with the Koada'Dal, the open wrists closing on her, and opening on him. He quickly concentatred and the regeration effect of the iksar closed the wounds, leaving a faint scar, and a few drops of green blood on the floor.<br><br>Culris then left the elf to her amusements, and he prepared the spell to distract the Tier'Dal while the mission was performed<br>&nbsp;<br>Culris Wurmbane<br>Lord of the Brood<br>Mithaniel Marr</td></tr>
