	   <tr><td colspan=2>With Culris fully restored to her, Usula began working on their plans for the nasty softskins known as the Tier Dal.&nbsp;&nbsp;She had heard of their great library and the many secret necromantic spells offered only in Neriak.  She also knew that if anything, Neriak was more unassailable than Kaladim had been.  While Culris consolidated Iksar supremacy over Kunark, Usula brought along Eizck (now her personal assistant) and headed to the Warsliks Woods.  Eizck, ever bold and curious, tried to pry information from Usula, but she was not forthcoming.<br><br>When they approached the docks, Eizck realized they must be either inspecting the new sea-going ships, or they were themselves going on a trip.  He somehow suspected the latter, as Usula seemed to be carrying a small pack with her.  She did not tell him to pack anything though, which was a bit of a surprise.  Then again, knowing her as he was beginning to, he wondered if she would just as soon live off the land.<br><br>Therefore, Eizck was not at all surprised when they both boarded one of the new ships, which already had a full crew of monk-sailors, and set out north.<br><br>Once the boat had departed, Usula was a little more forthcoming.<br><br><span style='color: green;'>&quot;We have need of a small reconnaissance mission into the heart of the Tier Dal territory.  As you are so familiar with softskin lands, and as I have such ability, we shall steal into Neriak and see whats about.&quot;</span style='color: green;'><br><br>&quot;Those lands are dangerous,&quot; Eizck warned &quot;even for one of your great power.&quot;<br><br>Usula smirked.  <span style='color: green;'>&quot;I have no great fear of the little softskins, and neither shall you.  We do nothing to let them know we are there, and they do nothing to see us.  They would not expect us to come into the heart of their power, especially since we made it so obvious our concerns were over Kunark.  I expect that Culris will be arranging matters so that the Tier Dal have other matters to worry about besides the guarding of the Third Gate.&quot;</span style='color: green;'><br><br>Eizck blinked.  It was a sure sign he thought Usula bereft of her senses.  Surely not even the great dragons would dare enter the deepest and darkest portion of Neriak.  Seeing this, however, Usula explained.<br><br><span style='color: green;'>&quot;Trust me Eizck, I have no desire to become a martyr.  We have to much important work to accomplish.&quot;</span style='color: green;'><br><br>Eizck shrugged, knowing that regardless of the outcome, he was bound to this powerful necromancer to whatever fate held.<br><br><br>After having dodged a few Elven vessels, the ship finally paused off the shore of the desert of North Ro.  Usula and Eizck dove in and swam to shore, whereupon, Usula quickly summoned a skeletal servant to carry her small bag.  Eizck, in the meantime, began to polish his weapons and clean his armor in an attempt to assure the salty water did not cause them damage.<br><br>Usula turned to Eizck and said, <span style='color: green;'>&quot;Now it is your turn to take me to the black forest and then on to the entrance of Neriak.  I do not expect you to enter in with me, as that would take great courage.&quot;</span style='color: green;'><br><br>Eizck led the way, and as he had anticipated, they lived off the small meals they were able to forage from the land.  Before the week was out, they were in the dark forests hiding the entrance of Neriak.<br><br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Sat Feb 16 17:00:08 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br>Usula Wurmbane<br>Iksar Necromancer<br>Empress of Fear</td></tr>
