	   <tr><td colspan=2>As &quot;Olunea&quot; rested on the wharf in the glowing sunshine she contemplated just what her next move should be.&nbsp;&nbsp;There had been no word of where Pusbag was or whether he was even alive, which was surprising due to the enormous portent of such information.  <i>If</i> he was alive the security of his confinement was very tight particularly since rumor was the coin of the realm in Norrath.  Such knowledge was valuable beyond belief in the right hands and ears, yet with no iota of scuttlebutt on anyone's tongue it was becoming increasingly likely Pusbag was truly dead after all.<br><br>Samisen had noted for weeks the passage of a dwarf who was a messenger between the office of Ironholm and the various arms of the bureaucracy running the city of New Freeport.  She took particular notice of how Ironholm's lackey would pass by a dark alley on his way to communicate with the many faceless drones intent on counting their beans.  <br><br>One of the thieves in her employ waited for the clueless dwarf to make his way from the Bureau of Foreign Affairs (where diplomatic dispatches originated once they arrived from Kaladim) to Ironhom's office, which took him past the thief's isolated ambush site.  Upon hearing the approaching footsteps of the message-laden dwarf, the rogue slipped out of the shadows and slid a poisoned blade between the ribs of the dwarf.  Immediately the body slumped silently in death into the arms of the rogue where he was carried into a dark room and divested of the bag of money, messenges, and financial statements he carried.  The bag was passed to a darkened figure dressed in identity hiding flowing robes who, upon receiving the pouch, disappeared from sight.  The dwarf's body was disposed of, near a tavern where he was known to frequent and engage in drinking contests.  A death of another dwarf in yet another drunken brawl would not be of interest to anyone, even if he was Ironhom's messenger.  What would be cause for alarm, however, would be the loss of the diplomatic pouch.  However, no clue would be left to its' location.<br><br>********************************************************<br><br>Sometime later Samisen met with Braag in a secret location and showed him a very important document.  It stated that Pusbag was indeed alive in Kaladim after being tortured at the hands of the Iksar and delivered to the dwarves as a peace offering from Usula.  He was to be held as a political prisoner until a decision could be made about his fate.  The page was signed by King Thex himself with his royal seal.  There were other items of interest such as the disposition of forces, numbers of supplies, total of wealth, some of which Samisen knew from her surveillence of New Freeport and her close association with Quick, the leading human councilmember.<br><br>After cursing that lizard-witch, the two Pusbag loyalists began to formulate a plan to rescue their King...<br><br>--Pusbag Infection<br>&nbsp;<br>Emperor and Shamanic High Priest of the Trolls<br>"Worship Innoruuk, you worthless cattle!"<br></td></tr>
