	   <tr><td colspan=2>Pusbag had been released from his bonds, but had been permanently detained in a room deep in the heart of Kaladim.&nbsp;&nbsp;Some form of long lasting magic had been cast on him and the fizzles which had become increasingly frequent had become a permanent fixture here in the dwarve's home city.  He could not cast a single successful &quot;Gate&quot; or even a lowly &quot;Summon Food&quot;.<br><br>With little food his stomach growled incessantly these past weeks and the little food that was given him was hardly palatable to his gourmet tastes.   No word had reached him of the fate of Grobb, Braag, or any of a thousand other concerns the former Troll King had, and so to hold boredom at arm's length he practiced the intricate kata his adopted human sister, Angiisan the monk, had taught him as a youngster.  He had always found it soothed him when he worried about various details of leadership.  If nothing else, it kept him in fighting shape if the opportunity to rip the heads off of some of his captors presented itself since he had no weapons.  <br><br>He wondered where his royal scepter was.  Who was wearing his incredible enchanted armor?  What faction was running Grobb?  Where was Usula, Braag, and Samisen?  Well, no use in speculating about things over which he had no control. <br><br>Pusbag continued to stew in his room and wait for others to decide his fate.<br><br>*************************************************************<br><br>Meanwhile Braag met with Samisen deep in the desert of Ro.  They shared information, ideas, and goods all the while keeping an eye on their surroundings.   They had no desire to be ambushed by a wandering Sand Giant, especially since they had become quite numerous since the fall of Freeport.  The presence of the huge monsters ensured that the meeting was kept secret.<br><br>Eventually the two nodded their heads and went their separate ways, Braag to the south and Samisen to the north.  Each had their ears open for any news of their leader, Pusbag Infection and longed to have him leading them in battle against their foes once again.  No word had leaked of his whereabouts as of yet, but they knew that such a secret could not be kept for long...<br><br>--Pusbag Infection<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Fri Feb 15 16:53:39 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br>Emperor and Shamanic High Priest of the Trolls<br>"Worship Innoruuk, you worthless cattle!"<br></td></tr>
