	   <tr><td colspan=2>/ooc on <br>Hopefully this helps set the stage for an invasion of Tier'Dal territory by the Iksar... at least a bunch of the guards are occupied now.<br>/ooc off<br><br>Bing, an old Druid friend of Phreda's father, was the first to notice the tromping sound coming from his right.&nbsp;&nbsp;Snickering, he poked the halfling next to him to get his attention.  &quot;I hear somebody coming, get ready to have some fun!&quot;  He tucked his half-eaten fishcake into a coat pocket to free his fingers for wiggling.  &quot;Do you have something to wash this down with?&quot;<br><br>His friend did not have time to reply.  A cry from the first human guard sent the other forty nine on a collision course with the halfling troop.  Cocky from their recent troll victory, they were caught completely off guard; the halflings all screamed incoherently and scattered!<br><br>Phreda, part of the front half of the caravan with the rest of the warriors, first heard the battle cry of a human guard, then a dozen screams of halfling terror behind her.  She turned around to witness chaos - halflings fleeing in every direction like a gnome's fireworks explosion.  Suddenly dozens of human guards were upon them.  Two warriors on either side of her were immediately slain with long, heavy swords.  Realizing the odds of the halflings surviving this skirmish were slim to none, Phreda followed her nose and ran, pausing only to run her claws through a guard attempting to intercept her.<br><br>She ran to the top of a very steep hill and steeled herself to meet the guard who chased her.  She got quite a headstart owing to natural halfling agility, not to mention the massive adrenaline rush from a deadly confrontation.  The guard gave a roar and swung his large sword straight at her jugular.  She ducked the sword and countered by slashing his midsection with her Icetooth claws.  Before he could swing a second time, she split the muscles of his left thigh.  The human lost his balance and tumbled down the rocks, head over heels, to the bottom of the hill.<br><br>Spent, Phreda sat hard onto the ground and surveyed the scene beyond.  Thankfully not many halflings laid motionless on the ground.  However, it appeared as if the humans were enjoying themselves too much.  Many laughed as they chased and terrorized the little folk, toying with them like naughty children trying to herd piglets.  <br><br>Phreda rubbed her eyes and sighed.  Their party was at least temporarily dissolved, they looked like fools, and more importantly, they lost some of their own.  She didn't know where she was in the forest; she had a compass, but was unaware of the location of sentry posts and other bad areas.  <br><br>Suddenly she felt a blade lift the hairs on the back of her neck.  Phreda froze.  A voice with a strange dialect said quietly, &quot;Look what we have here.... A brazen lass who brings evil to our home.  You don't belong here.  Answer for yourself!&quot;  Phreda slowly turned around and was shocked to see three strange halflings in tattered leather dress, all pointing daggers at her.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Fri Feb 15 04:26:51 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br>Phreda Biggles<br>20 Warrior, Bristlebane<br>Have bandages, will travel</td></tr>
