	   <tr><td colspan=2>Munc just had huffed and puffed his way back into the halfling territory when he heard the tromping of horses' hooves.&nbsp;&nbsp;Unsheathing his sword he slipped between the trees and saw humans (food!) driving the small people around in sport before dispatching some to the hereafter.  He quickly got behind some of the riders and swung his sword making a clean cut in the human's neck, causing it roll down the horse's back like a bowling ball.  Another went down due to the surprise attack and keen edge of Munc's blade.  Several more died to the deadly whirling metal, until the humans shouted out &quot;Retreat!  Retreat!&quot;  Turning around, Munc saw some movement in the bushes where a green leather-clad hobbit had a knife to the throat of one of the female halflings who several days earlier had pecked open wounds in his stout legs.  Reaching back, he drove the sharp point of the sword deep into the back of the green halfling, skewering him like a shishkabob.  The knife wielding halfling writhed briefly before giving up the ghost.  Munc quickly spoke to the wide-eyed lady halfling warrior standing in front of him, &quot;Me no hurt little snackies!  Me only want to talk to yoo!&quot;  Just as quickly, Munc threw his weapon down on the ground and opened his hands proving he was unarmed.  &quot;Munc need to see little snackies 'bout sumptin.  Me promise to not eat yoo!  No stream prej-dice pleeeeese!&quot;<br><br>As the humans and rouge halflings rode or ran off to escape the attack from the Troll, the original halfling war party surrounded Munc nervously fingering their blades or magical staves.  The richly dressed hobbit stepped forward and addressed Munc, &quot;Well?  What have you to say, foul creature?  It must be very important for you to have come back all that way just to die at our hands.  Speak!&quot;<br><br>With that invitation, Munc began to explain what had happened in Grobb and the treachery of the Iksar against his Emperor, Pusbag.  He was interupted several times by the halfling leader for clearer details causing Munc to start from the very beginning each time.  Very soon the halflings realized it was best to let the Troll finish his story, since he was dumber than a sack of hammers.  At his present rate it would be well into the evening before he finished his tale.  <br><br>Eventually Munc stopped speaking.  The silence was palpable since it was not yet clear why the Troll had come back to the Rivervale area.  &quot;Well?  Why did you come back here, Munc?&quot; asked Phreda, who was more feeling more kindly towards the Troll due to his intervention on her behalf.<br><br>&quot;Me want to be halfling now.  Me no more want to be Troll.  Trolls got bad king.  King Totem no good!  Me no more want to be Troll.  Me can lift good, help yoo fix snackie city, kill bad tings.  Me no eat yoo, me promise,&quot; answered Munc.<br><br>The halflings got in a big circle and began whispering, every once in a while poking a head up to give the Troll a frowning look.  Munc stood wringing his hands as he did when nervous, and dancing from foot to foot like he had to go to the bathroom.  Finally the leader walked up to the Troll.  &quot;Ok.  You must promise to serve us faithfully and never eat another hobbit.  That, and you have to revoke your evil ways and become a vegan-- that means you eat only plants.&quot;<br><br>Munc's face showed horror.<br><br>&quot;Oh, alright.  You may eat animals, but only those ones we tell you are acceptable to eat.  Rats and such.  You promise?&quot; asked the hobbit.<br><br>&quot;Yuh!  Yuh!  Munc promise!  Me make good snackie!&quot;<br><br>And with that the halflings got a major upgrade in their defense.  Munc stood guard, hauled trees, stone, lifted wooden beams, and cleared Rivervale of the brush which clogged the streets of the once-beautiful city.  He quickly slew the goblins which encroached on the western wall of Rivervale and secured the halfling's borders, much to the delight of the deputies assigned to guarding the hobbit complement.  Munc had never felt more at home.  More importantly, he felt he had made a friend with Phreda, something he never had before.  Soon, he tagged along behind her like a love-struck puppy whenever he finished whatever tasks assigned to him by the overseers.  Phreda was initially annoyed by the attention of the giant creature and the catcalls of her fellow warriors, but soon saw a different aspect to the friendly Troll's personality.  In his rapt devotion to the little halfling, he displayed a kindness rarely seen by even the most compassionate of her kind.  The two were soon fast friends and would seldom be seen not in the other's company. <br><br>--Pusbag Infection<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Fri Feb 15 16:28:50 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br>Emperor and Shamanic High Priest of the Trolls<br>"Worship Innoruuk, you worthless cattle!"<br></td></tr>
