	   <tr><td colspan=2>Late one morning Phreda and Munc were fishing in the river flowing through Rivervale.&nbsp;&nbsp;That is, Phreda was using a fishing pole and bait, and Munc was leaning his head close to the water, and yelling at any trout which happened to swim close by.  His troll visage combined with the sudden noise usually killed the fish outright.  He would then pluck the floating fish from the water and swallow it whole.  <br><br>Munc held to his promise of eating only smaller prey found in the area, but his stomach was in perpetual mid-grumble.  &quot;I miss da Grobb,&quot; Munc said, &quot;but da Grobb is a bad place.&quot;  Phreda put her pole away and sat down next to him.  They looked at each other and frowned.  &quot;Will Phreda snackie help Munc fix Grobb?&quot;  Munc asked plaintively.  <br><br>Phreda chewed on her lip thoughtfully.  Rivervale was restored more or less to its former state, and a messenger was already en route to invite the rest of its citizens home.  The town was dreadfully quiet, and Phanny wasn't there to provide her with common sense. &quot;You mean like an undercover operation?&quot;  she asked.  Munc furrowed his bristly brows.  &quot;We would have to be sneaky,&quot; she explained.  &quot;We can't just walk up and kill the bad guys.&quot;  Munc was clearly disappointed.  &quot;But we can kill bad guys in da Grobb if we're sneaky!&quot;<br><br>A few hours later, they set off toward the Troll Swamps. Munc was well laden with fishcakes and beer, and Phreda sat on his shoulders.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
