	   <tr><td colspan=2>When the Lunarsa reappeared in Usula's chambers, Icewind was with her.&nbsp;&nbsp;He bowed quite stiffly to the necromancer, but made no comment.  Usula looked pensive for the first time in her very long career, and she bowed low to the cleric of Tunare.<br><br>&quot;I would ask a boon of you Novastorm and offer something valuable in return.  In the chambers behind me lay the corpse of Culris Wurmbane, a necromancer you have known in your past.  He is very important to me, and I ask you raise him from death.&quot;<br><br>&quot;Why should I help you, dark <b>witch</b>?&quot; Icewind asked her a bit spitefully.<br><br>&quot;Because I have never invaded your lands.  While the Faydark sat ripe for the picking, I stayed my soldiers hands, and your forests were spared.  This however, it not what I wish to say.  Forgive me, it is not often when I ask a favor, and I have grown unused to anything other than immediate obedience.  I have no quarrel with you softskin elves, Icewind, and I can see to it that the Iksar never invade your forests.  I also offer whatever wealth or possessions I have.  Culris <i>must</i> live again.&quot;<br><br>&quot;Release my aunt from whatever beguilement you have placed upon her, and I shall consider your offer.&quot; Icewind retorted.<br><br>Aaean laughed.  &quot;I am under no beguilement nephew.  Usula and I have had an understanding since before you were conceived.  I saved her from goblins when she was just a hatchling, and she promised never to invade the Faydark in recompense.  She has always kept her pledges, always.  You may think it distasteful for me to associate with necromancers, but you forget that I am a wizardess, and not a follower of the All Mother.  Many is the time I have hunted with such as her, and always I do things of my own choosing, whether you wish to understand them or not.&quot;<br><br>Icewind glared at his aunt, wishing her words were false, even as his soul knew they were true.  &quot;Fine, swear never to set claws in the Faydark, Usula.  Promise no Iksar will come to the Faydark with the intent to harm my people, and I will resurrect Culris for you.&quot;<br><br>&quot;Thus I promise, Icewind.  You have my word as a member of the Wurmbane Brood.&quot; Usula responded quickly.<br><br>Icewind glared at her once more, then turned to his aunt.  &quot;Bring me back to the Faydark after this, aunt, and then forever banish yourself from my sight.&quot;<br><br>Aaean chuckled.<br><br>Icewind proceeded to the back halls Usula claimed as her private quarters and saw the corpse carefully cushioned on the floor.  Then he saw the head, or lack thereof, and gasped.  &quot;This will take a mighty blessing from Tunare to restore, Usula.  I pray you honor your bargain, or nothing shall save you from the wrath of the righteous.&quot;<br><br>Usula nodded, watching intently as the cleric began scribing mystic symbols into the air and chanting in the sing-song way of the elves.  An hour passed, then finally many strands of blue manna surrounded Culris, and before Usula could blink, he was standing, severely weakened and looking extremely tired, before her.<br><br>Without thought she rushed to Culris and gave him a hug.  He blanched, but then was surrounded by more strands of glowing blue magic.  He was healed.<br><br>Without a word to the necromancers, Icewind turned to is aunt and said, &quot;Take me from this house of death immediately.&quot;  Aaean complied and gated with Icewind to the Greater Faydark.<br><br>&quot;Culris, my lord, you are returned to me.  Now we must strike against the Tier Dal before they gain control of Antonica.  They were the only faction that did not participate in the debacle known as Pusbags Great Offensive.  Oh, before I forget, here are some new clothes I had crafted especially for you from the skin of the troll barbarian.  I have deemed the legionnaire we had been discussing as a true asset to our cause.  Soon enough, Kunark will be free!&quot;<br><br>/ooc on Just an interesting link regarding the meaning of Troll in Iksar, from the unabridged addition of Alaaraf's encyclopedia Iksari<br><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/races.html?race=13&amp;mid=100586350578646" target=_new>http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/races.html?race=13&amp;mid=100586350578646</a><br><br>&nbsp;<br>Usula Wurmbane<br>Iksar Necromancer<br>Empress of Fear</td></tr>
