<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101353357391349></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101353357391349><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=journal.html?user=2076&mid=101353357391349>Watching and Waiting</a> <a id=fs8 href=journal.html?user=2076&mid=101353357391349#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=2076><span id=Sage>Pusbag the Malevolent</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>1371 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Feb 12th 1:09 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Pusbag Infection, deposed King/Emperor of the Trolls and All Norrath, carefully observed all the goings on of the tasty creatures intent on hurting him.&nbsp;&nbsp;Surprising to anyone but himself, the only <i>real</i> discomfort was his stomach which remained perpetually half empty.  Yes, the tortures and pain inflicted on him were uncomfortable, even excruciating at times, but what that traitorous whelp, Usula did not seem to understand was he <i>enjoyed</i> the sharp sensations of hurt coursing through his nerve endings.  While the immediate pain was undesirable, the surge of adrenaline it produced afterwards was liberating and intoxicating.  He laughed to himself.  This showed beyond a shadow of a doubt that gecko which posed as a Empress had no idea what made Trolls-- and especially him -- tick.  He had been inflicting pain on himself since he was old enough to do so simply for the sheer joy of it.<br><br>Granted, the flaying of his flesh was trememdously painful, but Pusbag had reached new levels of ecstasy at the same time.  He only wished these vermin holding him would feed him a decent meal, because the only thing which truly bothered him was the constant gnawing of his stomach which remained forever empty.  Having all these Happy Meals walking just out of his reach was the <i>real</i> torture.  <br><br>Usula.   Hmmmmm.  She betrayed him both in word and deed.  How would he turn this to his advantage?  He had lost literally everything from his kingdom to his clothes, yet he had been here before.  He started out as a poor Troll with nothing, so this was nothing new.  But that did not mean he intended on staying here depending on the good will of these <i>cattle</i> to survive.  He needed a plan.<br><br>He noted that the Iksar and now the dwarves had bound and gagged him to prevent him using his tremendous magical powers by voice or finger waving.  That option for now was blocked.  He had recovered from the injuries gained by the tender loving ministrations of that Iksar/salamander's torturing due to his inate regenerative abilities, so he had much of his legendary strength back, but now was not a time to test the power of those who held him captive.  Indeed, if he could get some mild pain inflicted on himself he could easily double his strength with the rush he got with raw nerves.<br><br>He elected to play it safe for now and pretend to be groggy and helpless, just as he had back in Kunark.  <i>Whew!</i>  Yet that axe had just about ended everything when he arrived in Kaladim.  <i>That</i> was a close call.<br><br>He took stock of where things were at the moment.  Grobb was, as far as he knew, in the hands of Usula.  Beyond that he really knew nothing.  Were the rest of his loyal comrades still alive?  Had all his coffer and treasuries been emptied?  Most likely, he thought ruefully, at that last question.  The remaining issue then was how would this play out?  No telling since he was at the mercy of these cursed cattle at the hands of his new arch-enemy.  Given the chance he would return the favor and make a nice bathrobe from that Skink's skin.  Usula would pay if Innoruuk gave him the chance.  His hate began to burn in his chest fueling his will to live.  <br><br>Only time would tell how this would play out and he wasn't dead yet...<br><br>--Pusbag Infection<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Tue Feb 12 12:16:18 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br>Emperor and Shamanic High Priest of the Trolls<br>"Worship Innoruuk, you worthless cattle!"<br></td></tr>
