	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>/ooc - for anyone reading this journal, and wondering how in the world Pusbag ended up in Kaladim, refer to the journal of Mugali (Legends of Norrath - Alternate History).&nbsp;&nbsp;You might also want to check out the journal of Tochail, where this all began.  An Warric's jounrnal.  And others, you have to hunt around to get the full story.  Thanks to Usula for giving me this &quot;bone&quot; to write about.  It is most unexpected.<br><br>/ooc on<br><br>Guard Dunil and Guard Dunn were enjoying their rotation at the entrance to mighty Kaladim.  guard duty here was easier then at the crossroads; or another of the remote outposts in the Butcherblock.  The day usually consisted of checking visitors to Kaladim and ridding the Butcherblock Mountains of the occassional wandering curse of Cazic-Thule, the skeleton.  Around noon an initiate of Brell, that Guard Dunn had been courting, would bring the two Stormguard warriors some ale and cheese.  It was good to be home.  That was about to change.<br><br>Guards Dunn and Dunil drew their weapons when the air before them abruptly began to crackle and hiss.  Blue arcing magic seemingly burst out of the air before them, followed by a large slumped over Troll.  The Troll, a dazed look on his face fell straight forward, and collapsed in the dirt in front of Kaladim.  Guard Dunn ran forward with his battle axe raised high, ready to deliver the killing blow to ancient, hated, enemy of the Dwarves.  <br><br>&quot;Wait! Dunn stop!&quot;, Guard Dunil screamed after his friend.  Dunn's blow veered at the last moment and the axe buried itself deep into the dirt near the Troll's head.  A crowd of Dwarven citizens and visiting Elves and Gnomes began to gather. <br><br>Guard Dunil walked up to the motionless Troll and poked him with his foot.  A low moan escaped from the Troll, and the crowd stepped back several steps.  This obviously was not a normal Troll.  Even for a male, he was a least a foot taller than the average Troll.  Even though his skin appeared to be unmarked, one who knew Trolls would be able to discern that this Troll had been horribly tortured.<br><br>Guard Dunil turned to his partner,&quot;Dunn, summon the guard and fetch Canloe Nusback.  Strange omens find this Troll at our doorstep.  The King will want to question him.  Hurry now!&quot;<br><br>Guard Dunn ran into Kaladim, and soon a dozen members of the Stormguard poured out.  A few minutes later, Canloe Nusback arrived.  The Stormguard had rolled the Troll over onto his back.  He looked much like a dead green cow, his girth adding a new hill to the Butcherblock Mountains.  Canloe stopped a few feet from the troll, his jaw dropping in astonishment.  Quickly he came out of his lull and began snapping orders.<br><br>The Troll was bound thrice over with the strongest ropes.  Canloe instructed the Stormguard to gag him tightly also.  Then he had the guards at the entrance quadrupled.  He spied a Fier'Dal ranger in the crowd, one of Faydark's Champions, and pulled him aside.  As Canloe whispered instructions in the young ranger's ear, the Elf's eyes grew wide until it seemed they would pop out of his head.  When Canloe finished the Elf sprinted away and dissapeared into the hills, as was their way, in the direction of Greater Faydark.<br><br>The Troll was carried into Kaladim and bound to a post in the arena.  His gags were tightened once again.  Barrtih the Brave, the greatest living Dwarven warrior stepped forward, pushing through the guards surrounding the Troll.  The Troll's eyes opened, he moaned, tried to move, but failed, then scanned his surroundings.  A mixture of apprehension and malice crossed his face.  He made another futile attempt to stuggle against his bonds, gave up, and settled his eyes on Barrith.<br><br>Reaching into a pouch at his belt, Barrith began to fill a pipe.  A broad smile stretched across his face.  &quot;Pusbag Infection, King of the Trolls, prisoner of Kaladim.&quot;, Barrith plainly stated and began to laugh.  &quot;Who would have thought?  The King will be most interested in this.  What has happened to your kingdom, Troll?  How far you have fallen?&quot;  Barrith laughed again and stared back at Pusbag, the fallen Troll Emperor.  He puffed on his pipe, chuckling at the misfortune that brought the great Pusbag to this.<br><br>__________________________<br><br><br>A council was convened.  Stormguard thoughout the Butcherblock were tripled.  Pusbag was kept, bound a gagged, in the arena.  Barrith and a horde of Stormguard stood watch over him.  High priests of Brell were on hand in case the Troll somehow attempted any magics.  The next day, the King of the Elves and Gnomes would arrive, and along with the King of the Dwarves, the interrogation of Pusbag Infection would begin.<br><br>Ironhom Hammerforge<br>Dwarven Paladin<br>Tallon Zek Server<br>&nbsp;<br>Judd Jaggedoak <br>(deceased)<br>Wood Elf Ranger<br><br><br><br><br></td></tr>
